<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-20T04:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-20T04:35:00-05:00" n="1328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1328">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/7–2045: Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 1328<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_MW2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Murray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-20T13:00:00+03:25">July 20, 1945—1
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>511. Speaking in Majlis yesterday Deputy <persName corresp="#p_ANQ1">Ardalan</persName> urged early withdrawal British and Soviet
                                troops in accordance Article 5 Tripartite Treaty.<note n="1" xml:id="d1328fn1">i. e., the Anglo-Soviet-Iranian treaty of
                                    January 29, 1942. Text in Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>, p.
                                    249.</note> Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_SM1">Sadr</persName> replied that govt agreed and was studying
                                problem.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_MW2"><hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>